description: Java class representing a Resume entity stored in MongoDB, including fields for user information, skills, keywords, and timestamps.

classes.name: Resume
classes.description: Entity class mapping to MongoDB collection 'resumes', representing parsed resume data with metadata fields.

methods.name: getUserId
methods.description: Returns the ID of the user associated with the resume.

methods.name: getUploadId
methods.description: Returns the upload ID linked to this resume.

methods.name: getFullText
methods.description: Returns the full text content of the resume.

methods.name: getSkills
methods.description: Returns the list of skills extracted from the resume.

methods.name: getKeywords
methods.description: Returns the list of keywords associated with the resume.

methods.name: getCreatedAt
methods.description: Returns the creation timestamp of the resume record.

methods.name: setUserId
methods.description: Sets the user ID associated with the resume.

methods.name: setUploadId
methods.description: Sets the upload ID for this resume.

methods.name: setFullText
methods.description: Sets the full text content of the resume.
